widevin vendors Devin/Cascade protocol `.proto` files from:

https://github.com/can1357/oh-my-pi

Vendored source path in upstream snapshot:

packages/ai/src/providers/devin/proto

The provider behavior, OAuth exchange, and model discovery implementation were informed by these upstream files:

packages/ai/src/providers/devin.ts
packages/ai/src/registry/oauth/devin.ts
packages/catalog/src/discovery/devin.ts

The vendored protocol files are included for interoperability and maintenance reference.

The minimal Prost message definitions in `rust/src/proto.rs` reproduce only
the field numbers and wire types used by this project from those vendored
protocol files. They are committed source, so Rust consumers do not need
`protoc` or Buf.
